# Post Copier To-Do's for the `{{ module_type }}/{{ module_name }}/{{ etl_name }}` ETL process

This issue is for tracking the development of the ETL process that was copied from the `able-workflow-etl-copier` template.

Each of the sections below could be separated into a sub-issue. After each sub-issue, all tests should still pass.

## 1. Write a draft of the rule(s) in the `workflow/rules/{{ module_type }}/{{ module_name }}.smk` file

If the ETL process will be running multiple times for different files, define a `{{ module_type }}_{{ module_name }}_{{ etl_name }}_run` rule with [wildcards](https://snakemake.readthedocs.io/en/stable/snakefiles/rules.html#wildcards), and then a `{{ module_type }}_{{ module_name }}_{{ etl_name }}_all` rule that uses the [`expand()`](https://snakemake.readthedocs.io/en/stable/snakefiles/rules.html#the-expand-function) function in the input section to specify the output files to be produced by the `{{ module_type }}_{{ module_name }}_{{ etl_name }}_run` rule.

1. `{{ module_type }}_{{ module_name }}_{{ etl_name }}_run` rule

   This rule should define the input files that a single run of this ETL process will produce.

2. `{{ module_type }}_{{ module_name }}_{{ etl_name }}_all` rule

   This rule expands values into the wildcards to produce all the expected files.

At this point, this draft rule will not be run, but is just an opportunity to specify what the expected inputs and outputs are of a single run of the ETL process.

